{"timestamp": "2026-05-27 16:59:56,832", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nYou are a workflow planning agent.\\nYour task is to:\\n-\\\"Analyze the job description\\\",\\n    \\\"Analyze the candidate resume\\\",\\n    \\\"Conduct technical interview\\\",\\n    \\\"Send emails as and when needed\\\",\\n    \\\"Score candidate responses\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate final evaluation report\\\"\\n\\nReturn the output as a .txt file of all the steps taken to perform the tasks.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task0:\\n  Objective: Extract key evaluation criteria from the job description\\n  Result: ```json\\n{\\n  \\\"job_description_evaluation_criteria\\\": [\\n    \\\"Technical Skills\\\",\\n    \\\"Problem-solving abilities\\\",\\n    \\\"Communication skills\\\",\\n    \\\"Experience\\\",\\n    \\\"Cultural fit\\\",\\n    \\\"Teamwork\\\",\\n    \\\"Leadership\\\",\\n    \\\"Adaptability\\\",\\n    \\\"Specific technologies proficiency\\\",\\n    \\\"Domain knowledge\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task5:\\n  Objective: Generate final evaluation report by combining interview transcripts and scored responses\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nDevelop scoring algorithm for candidate interview responses based on extracted criteria\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\ndef score_candidate_response(response, criteria_weights, keywords):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Scores a candidate's interview response based on predefined criteria and keywords.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        response (str): The candidate's interview response text.\\n        criteria_weights (dict): A dictionary mapping evaluation criteria to their weights.\\n                                  Example: {\\\"Technical Skills\\\": 0.25, \\\"Problem-solving abilities\\\": 0.20, ...}\\n        keywords (dict): A dictionary mapping evaluation criteria to a list of relevant keywords.\\n                         Example: {\\\"Technical Skills\\\": [\\\"python\\\", \\\"algorithm\\\", \\\"data structure\\\"], \\\"Problem-solving abilities\\\": [\\\"debugging\\\", \\\"optimization\\\", \\\"testing\\\"], ...}\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        dict: A dictionary containing the scores for each evaluation criterion and the overall score.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    response = response.lower()\\n    scores = {}\\n    overall_score = 0\\n\\n    for criterion, weight in criteria_weights.items():\\n        scores[criterion] = 0\\n        if criterion in keywords:\\n            relevant_keywords = keywords[criterion]\\n            keyword_count = 0\\n            for keyword in relevant_keywords:\\n                if keyword in response:\\n                    keyword_count += 1\\n            scores[criterion] = keyword_count / len(relevant_keywords) if len(relevant_keywords) > 0 else 0\\n        overall_score += scores[criterion] * weight\\n\\n    scores[\\\"overall_score\\\"] = overall_score\\n    return scores\\n\\ndef example_usage():\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Provides an example of how to use the scoring function.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    example_response = \\\"I have extensive experience with Python and data structures. I also have experience in debugging and optimizing code.\\\"\\n    example_criteria_weights = {\\n        \\\"Technical Skills\\\": 0.4,\\n        \\\"Problem-solving abilities\\\": 0.3,\\n        \\\"Communication skills\\\": 0.1,\\n        \\\"Experience\\\": 0.2\\n    }\\n    example_keywords = {\\n        \\\"Technical Skills\\\": [\\\"python\\\", \\\"algorithm\\\", \\\"data structure\\\"],\\n        \\\"Problem-solving abilities\\\": [\\\"debugging\\\", \\\"optimization\\\", \\\"testing\\\"],\\n        \\\"Experience\\\": [\\\"years of experience\\\", \\\"project\\\", \\\"worked on\\\"]\\n    }\\n\\n    scores = score_candidate_response(example_response, example_criteria_weights, example_keywords)\\n    print(scores)\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    example_usage()\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-27T16:59:56.832418\"\n}"}
