{"timestamp": "2026-05-27 17:00:10,144", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-27T17:00:10.144020\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Develop scoring algorithm for candidate interview responses based on extracted criteria\", \"result\": \"```python\\ndef score_candidate_response(response, criteria_weights, keywords):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Scores a candidate's interview response based on predefined criteria and keywords.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        response (str): The candidate's interview response text.\\n        criteria_weights (dict): A dictionary mapping evaluation criteria to their weights.\\n                                  Example: {\\\"Technical Skills\\\": 0.25, \\\"Problem-solving abilities\\\": 0.20, ...}\\n        keywords (dict): A dictionary mapping eva...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n1. The current implementation assigns zero scores to criteria that lack keyword lists (e.g., “Communication skills”), which may not reflect actual candidate performance.\\n2. Overall score is not normalized to a consistent scale (e.g., 0–100).\\n3. There’s no provision for manual scoring or default behavior when keyword lists are empty.\\n4. Matching is simplistic (substring matching), which may spur false positives/negatives; consider word boundaries.\\n5. No support for weighting individual keywords differently.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\nimport re\\n\\ndef score_candidate_response(response, criteria_weights, keywords, manual_scores=None, keyword_weights=None):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Scores a candidate's interview response based on predefined criteria, keywords, and optional manual inputs.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        response (str): The candidate's interview response text.\\n        criteria_weights (dict): Mapping evaluation criteria to their weights (sum should be 1.0).\\n                                 e.g. {\\\"Technical Skills\\\": 0.4, \\\"Problem-solving\\\": 0.3, ...}\\n        keywords (dict): Mapping criteria to a list of relevant keywords.\\n                       e.g. {\\\"Technical Skills\\\": [\\\"python\\\", \\\"algorithm\\\"], ...}\\n        manual_scores (dict, optional): Mapping criteria to manual scores (0–1) when keyword lists are absent or as override.\\n                                       e.g. {\\\"Communication\\\": 0.8}\\n        keyword_weights (dict, optional): Mapping criteria to dict of individual keyword weights.\\n                                        e.g. {\\\"Technical Skills\\\": {\\\"python\\\":0.7, \\\"algorithm\\\":0.3}, ...}\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        dict: Scores per criterion, raw overall score (0–1), and normalized score (0–100).\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    if manual_scores is None:\\n        manual_scores = {}\\n    if keyword_weights is None:\\n        keyword_weights = {}\\n\\n    text = response.lower()\\n    # tokenize on word boundaries to avoid substring mismatches\\n    tokens = re.findall(r\\\"\\\\b\\\\w+\\\\b\\\", text)\\n    scores = {}\\n    raw_overall = 0.0\\n\\n    for criterion, weight in criteria_weights.items():\\n        # 1) Manual override or default when no keywords\\n        if criterion in manual_scores and 0 <= manual_scores[criterion] <= 1:\\n            score = manual_scores[criterion]\\n        else:\\n            kw_list = keywords.get(criterion, [])\\n            if not kw_list:\\n                # no keywords and no manual score—assign zero\\n                score = 0.0\\n            else:\\n                # use individual keyword weights if provided\\n                kw_weights = keyword_weights.get(criterion, {kw: 1.0 for kw in kw_list})\\n                total_kw_weight = sum(kw_weights.get(kw, 1.0) for kw in kw_list)\\n                matched_weight = 0.0\\n                for kw in kw_list:\\n                    if kw.lower() in tokens:\\n                        matched_weight += kw_weights.get(kw, 1.0)\\n                score = matched_weight / total_kw_weight if total_kw_weight > 0 else 0.0\\n\\n        scores[criterion] = round(score, 3)\\n        raw_overall += score * weight\\n\\n    # normalize overall to percentage scale\\n    overall_percent = round(raw_overall * 100, 2)\\n    scores[\\\"overall_score_raw\\\"] = round(raw_overall, 3)\\n    scores[\\\"overall_score_pct\\\"] = overall_percent\\n\\n    return scores\\n\\ndef example_usage():\\n    example_response = (\\n        \\\"I have 5 years of experience working with Python algorithms and data structures. \\\"\\n        \\\"I excel at debugging, optimization, and clear communication with stakeholders.\\\"\\n    )\\n    criteria_weights = {\\n        \\\"Technical Skills\\\": 0.4,\\n        \\\"Problem-solving\\\": 0.3,\\n        \\\"Communication\\\": 0.2,\\n        \\\"Experience\\\": 0.1\\n    }\\n    keywords = {\\n        \\\"Technical Skills\\\": [\\\"python\\\", \\\"algorithm\\\", \\\"data\\\", \\\"structure\\\"],\\n        \\\"Problem-solving\\\": [\\\"debugging\\\", \\\"optimization\\\", \\\"testing\\\"],\\n        \\\"Experience\\\": [\\\"years\\\", \\\"experience\\\", \\\"worked\\\"],\\n        # Communication has no keywords: rely on manual scoring\\n    }\\n    manual_scores = {\\n        \\\"Communication\\\": 0.9\\n    }\\n    keyword_weights = {\\n        \\\"Technical Skills\\\": {\\\"python\\\": 0.5, \\\"algorithm\\\": 0.3, \\\"data\\\": 0.1, \\\"structure\\\": 0.1},\\n        \\\"Problem-solving\\\": {\\\"debugging\\\": 0.5, \\\"optimization\\\": 0.3, \\\"testing\\\": 0.2},\\n    }\\n\\n    scores = score_candidate_response(\\n        example_response,\\n        criteria_weights,\\n        keywords,\\n        manual_scores=manual_scores,\\n        keyword_weights=keyword_weights\\n    )\\n\\n    print(\\\"Candidate Scores:\\\", scores)\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    example_usage()\\n```\"}"}
