on\\ndef score_candidate_response(response, criteria_weights, keywords):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Scores a candidate's interview response based on predefined criteria and keywords.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        response (str): The candidate's interview response text.\\n        criteria_weights (dict): A dictionary mapping evaluation criteria to their weights.\\n                                  Example: {\\\"Technical Skills\\\": 0.25, \\\"Problem-solving abilities\\\": 0.20, ...}\\n        keywords (dict): A dictionary mapping evaluation criteria to a list of relevant keywords.\\n                         Example: {\\\"Technical Skills\\\": [\\\"python\\\", \\\"algorithm\\\", \\\"data structure\\\"], \\\"Problem-solving abilities\\\": [\\\"debugging\\\", \\\"optimization\\\", \\\"testing\\\"], ...}\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        dict: A dictionary containing the scores for each evaluation criterion and the overall score.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    response = response.lower()\\n    scores = {}\\n    overall_score = 0\\n\\n    for criterion, weight in criteria_weights.items():\\n        scores[criterion] = 0\\n        if criterion in keywords:\\n            relevant_keywords = keywords[criterion]\\n            keyword_count = 0\\n            for keyword in relevant_keywords:\\n                if keyword in response:\\n                    keyword_count += 1\\n            scores[criterion] = keyword_count / len(relevant_keywords) if len(relevant_keywords) > 0 else 0\\n        overall_score += scores[criterion] * weight\\n\\n    scores[\\\"overall_score\\\"] = overall_score\\n    return scores\\n\\ndef example_usage():\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Provides an example of how to use the scoring function.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    example_response = \\\"I have extensive experience with Python and data structures. I also have experience in debugging and optimizing code.\\\"\\n    example_criteria_weights = {\\n        \\\"Technical Skills\\\": 0.4,\\n        \\\"Problem-solving abilities\\\": 0.3,\\n        \\\"Communication skills\\\": 0.1,\\n        \\\"Experience\\\": 0.2\\n    }\\n    example_keywords = {\\n        \\\"Technical Skills\\\": [\\\"python\\\", \\\"algorithm\\\", \\\"data structure\\\"],\\n        \\\"Problem-solving abilities\\\": [\\\"debugging\\\", \\\"optimization\\\", \\\"testing\\\"],\\n        \\\"Experience\\\": [\\\"years of experience\\\", \\\"project\\\", \\\"worked on\\\"]\\n    }\\n\\n    scores = score_candidate_response(example_response, example_criteria_weights, example_keywords)\\n    print(scores)\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    example_usage()\\n```\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Develop technical interview module to conduct Q&A based on criteria and candidate profile\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport random\\n\\ndef generate_technical_questions(job_criteria, candidate_profile):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Generate technical interview questions based on job criteria and candidate profile.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        job_criteria (list of str): Key evaluation criteria extracted from the job description.\\n        candidate_profile (dict): Candidate resume details including skills, experience, projects.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list of str: A customized list of interview questions.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    questions = []\\n\\n    # 1. Technical Skills questions\\n    if \\\"Technical Skills\\\" in job_criteria:\\n        for tech in candidate_profile.get(\\\"skills\\\", []):\\n            questions.append(\\n                f\\\"Can you describe your experience with {tech}? \\\"\\n                \\\"What were the main challenges and how did you overcome them?\\\"\\n            )\\n\\n    # 2. Problem-solving / algorithm questions\\n    if \\\"Problem-solving abilities\\\" in job_criteria:\\n        questions.append(\\n            \\\"Describe a complex technical problem you solved. \\\"\\n            \\\"What was your approach to ensure correctness and efficiency?\\\"\\n        )\\n\\n    # 3. Experience-based questions\\n    if \\\"Experience\\\" in job_criteria:\\n        for exp in candidate_profile.get(\\\"work_experience\\\", []):\\n            title = exp.get(\\\"job_title\\\", \\\"your role\\\")\\n            company = exp.get(\\\"company\\\", \\\"your company\\\")\\n            questions.append(\\n                f\\\"You worked as a {title} at {company}. \\\"\\n                \\\"Can you walk me through a significant project there and your technical approach?\\\"\\n            )\\n\\n    # 4. Project-based questions\\n    for proj in candidate_profile.get(\\\"projects\\\", []):\\n        name = proj.get(\\\"project_name\\\", \\\"a project\\\")\\n        desc = proj.get(\\\"description\\\", \\\"\\\")\\n        questions.append(\\n            f\\\"Regarding your project '{name}', you mentioned: {desc} \\\"\\n            \\\"What architecture did you choose and why?\\\"\\n        )\\n\\n    # 5. Design questions\\n    if \\\"Specific technologies proficiency\\\" in job_criteria or \\\"Technical Skills\\\" in job_criteria:\\n        questions.append(\\n            \\\"Design a simple microservice for a real-time chat application. \\\"\\n            \\\"What components would you include and how would they interact?\\\"\\n        )\\n\\n    # 6. Leadership / teamwork questions\\n    if \\\"Leadership\\\" in job_criteria or \\\"Teamwork\\\" in job_criteria:\\n        questions.append(\\n            \\\"Tell me about a time you led or collaborated closely with a technical team. \\\"\\n            \\\"How did you ensure effective communication and delivery?\\\"\\n        )\\n\\n    # 7. Communication skills\\n    if \\\"Communication skills\\\" in job_criteria:\\n        questions.append(\\n            \\\"How do you ensure clear and effective communication when explaining technical concepts \\\"\\n            \\\"to non-technical stakeholders?\\\"\\n        )\\n\\n    # 8. Adaptability\\n    if \\\"Adaptability\\\" in job_criteria:\\n        questions.append(\\n            \\\"Tell me about a time you had to learn a new technology or process quickly. \\\"\\n            \\\"How did you approach it and what was the outcome?\\\"\\n        )\\n\\n    # Shuffle to mix question types\\n    random.shuffle(questions)\\n    return questions\\n\\ndef conduct_technical_interview(job_criteria, candidate_profile):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Conducts the technical interview by generating questions and collecting responses.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        job_criteria (list of str): Evaluation criteria.\\n        candidate_profile (dict): Candidate details.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        tuple:\\n            questions (list of str): Generated questions.\\n            responses (list of str): Candidate's answers.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    questions = generate_technical_questions(job_criteria, candidate_profile)\\n    responses = []\\n\\n    print(\\\"---- Technical Interview ----\\\")\\n    for i, q in enumerate(questions, start=1):\\n        print(f\\\"\\\\nQ{i}: {q}\\\")\\n        ans = input(\\\"Your response: \\\").strip()\\n        responses.append(ans)\\n\\n    print(\\\"\\\\nInterview complete. Responses collected.\\\")\\n    return questions, responses\\n\\ndef technical_interview_module(job_description_criteria, candidate_resume):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Conducts a technical interview based on job criteria and candidate profile.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        job_description_criteria (dict): Contains 'job_description_evaluation_criteria' key.\\n        candidate_resume (dict): Contains 'candidate_profile' key.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        tuple:\\n            questions (list of str): Generated questions.\\n            responses (list of str): Collected responses.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    job_criteria = job_description_criteria[\\\"job_description_evaluation_criteria\\\"]\\n    candidate_profile = candidate_resume[\\\"candidate_profile\\\"]\\n    return conduct_technical_interview(job_criteria, candidate_profile)\\n\\n# Example usage\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    job_description_criteria = {\\n        \\\"job_description_evaluation_criteria\\\": [\\n            \\\"Technical Skills\\\",\\n            \\\"Problem-solving abilities\\\",\\n            \\\"Communication skills\\\",\\n            \\\"Experience\\\",\\n            \\\"Teamwork\\\",\\n            \\\"Leadership\\\",\\n            \\\"Adaptability\\\",\\n            \\\"Specific technologies proficiency\\\"\\n        ]\\n    }\\n    candidate_resume = {\\n        \\\"candidate_profile\\\": {\\n            \\\"skills\\\": [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"Docker\\\", \\\"AWS\\\", \\\"Kubernetes\\\"],\\n            \\\"work_experience\\\": [\\n                {\\\"job_title\\\": \\\"DevOps Engineer\\\", \\\"company\\\": \\\"CloudCorp\\\"}\\n            ],\\n            \\\"projects\\\": [\\n                {\\n                    \\\"project_name\\\": \\\"Deployment Pipeline\\\",\\n                    \\\"description\\\": \\\"Built CI/CD pipeline using Jenkins and Docker.\\\"\\n                }\\n            ]\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    qs, rs = technical_interview_module(job_description_criteria, candidate_resume)\\n    # Save the questions and responses to a text file\\n    with open(\\\"technical_interview_transcript.txt\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n        f.write(\\\"Generated Questions:\\\\n\\\")\\n        for q in qs:\\n            f.write(f\\\"- {q}\\\\n\\\")\\n        f.write(\\\"\\\\nCollected Responses:\\\\n\\\")\\n        for r in rs:\\n            f.write(f\\\"- {r}\\\\n\\\")\\n\\n    print(\\\"\\\\nGenerated Questions and Collected Responses saved to technical_interview_transcript.txt\\\")\\n```\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nNo downstream objectives available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nGenerate final evaluation report by combining interview transcripts and scored responses\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPlain text\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```text\\n1. Analyze the job description to extract key requirements and evaluation criteria.\\n2. Analyze the candidate's resume to identify relevant skills, experience, and projects.\\n3. Use the job description criteria and candidate profile to generate technical interview questions using the `generate_technical_questions` function from the technical interview module.\\n4. Conduct the technical interview by presenting the generated questions to the candidate and recording their responses using the `conduct_technical_interview` function.\\n5. Save the interview transcript (questions and answers) to a text file.\\n6. For each candidate response, use the `score_candidate_response` function to generate a score based on predefined criteria weights and keywords. The criteria weights and keywords should be aligned with the job description.\\n7. Combine the interview transcript and the scored responses into a final evaluation report. The report should include the questions asked, the candidate's responses, the scores for each criterion, and the overall score.\\n8. Rank the candidates based on their overall scores from the evaluation reports.\\n9. Send emails to the candidates to inform them of the interview results. This step is external.\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-27T17:01:33.699076\"\n}"}
